		</p>

		<p class="page-design__our-experience">
			<span>Route</span>
			<div class="page-design__our-experience__route">
				<p>
					We took a bus from Quito to the bus station near the border and taxi to the border and then crossed the border on foot and grabbed a cab on the Colombia side to the other bus station in Ipiales to Popayan. After a couple nights in Popayan we went to Cali. From Cali we took a bus to Salento where we spent 3 nights at an eco lodge and then jumped in a mini-bus to Medellin. 
				</p>
				<p>
					From Medellin we took a 1.5 hour flight up to Santa Marta, the bus would have taken the better part of a day. We then went to a small town called Minca and then ended our trip with 5 amazing days in Cartagena.       
				</p>
			</div>
		</p>

		<p class="page-design__our-experience">
			<span>The Good</span>
			<ul class="page-design__our-experience--list">
				<li><strong>The people, the food, the vibe.</strong> For the amount of hardship this country has gone through in their recent history, they are lovely, happy people. I would live here if I could. Do not let the stories scare you from discovering this amazing country.</li>
				<li><strong>The prices are right.</strong> With the exception of Cartagena, Colombia is extremely affordable while at the same time getting great value for your money. Colombia is a mini-heaven for backpackers. </li>  
				<li>It is not yet booming with tourism. There has been a noticeable increase in the last few years, but you still feel like <strong>you are experiencing authentic Colombia. </strong></li>    
			</ul>
		</p>
		<p class="page-design__our-experience">
			<span>The Bad</span>
			<ul class="page-design__our-experience--list">
				<li>Not much. The main issue is that crime may be more potent in some areas vs other countries, but this should not be a deal breaker for you. Simply be a bit more careful with your belongings and the neighbourhoods you enter and you'll be completely fine. </li> 
			</ul>
		</p>
		<p class="page-design__our-experience">
			<span>The Verdict</span>
			<p class="section-headers__line-highlight section-headers__line-highlight--smaller">
				If we could pick one country to visit a second time, it would be Colombia. We absolutely loved it and would highly recommend it to anyone who is able to visit. There is also a variety of landscapes to visit from the Amazon to snow-capped mountains and beaches, there’s something for everyone. Plan to spend an extended period of time in Colombia.  
			</p>
		</p>
